# Silica Modal

This repository contains the code for the Silica Modal project.

## Prerequisites

- [Anaconda](https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual) installed

## Setup

1. Install Anaconda by following the instructions provided on the [Anaconda website](https://www.anaconda.com/products/individual).

2. Clone the repository:

    ```shell
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/silica-modal.git
    ```

3. Change into the project directory:

    ```shell
    cd /Users/tompritsky/projects/silica/silica/modal/abnumber
    ```

4. Create a new Conda environment from the YAML file:

    ```shell
    conda env create -f environment.yml -n silica-modal
    ```

5. Activate the Conda environment:

    ```shell
    conda activate silica-modal
    ```

## Usage

To run the "modal" command-line tool, use the following command. Note, for scheme you can use imgt, chothia, kabat, or aho. For seq, you can pass a single sequence as a string (for single submission) or a CSV file with all sequences in the first column (for batch submission).:
```modal run test_modal.py --scheme "imgt" --seq "test_modal_seqs.csv"
```




